Peru Stocks: Volcan, Southern Copper, Candente, Minsur, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-09T21:48:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/peru-stocks-volcan-southern-copper-candente-minsur-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for a third session, dropping
1.2 percent to 22,167.65. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid
0.9 percent to 3,029.38.  Miners dropped as metals declined in New York and  London ,
said Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based Juan Magot y
Asociados SAB.    Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, plunged 7.4 percent to $1.88. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA
(VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, fell 2.7 percent to
4.35 soles after Celfin Capital analyst Isabel Darrigrandi cut
the stock’s rating to “hold” from “buy.”  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1
PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, dropped 2.2
percent to 4.50 soles.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s
biggest copper producer, fell for a fourth session, losing 1.8
percent to $40, a five-month low.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, dropped 3.8 percent to 2.05 soles after crude
fell for a second day in New York.    Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, fell 2.1 percent to 16 soles after
sugar dropped in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  